Wayne Rooney of DC United. JOHANNESBURG - Former Manchester United captain Wayne Rooney rolled back the years with a stunning long-range goal against Orlando City on Wednesday. The stunning effort came in the 10th minute when the Englishman picked up a loose ball in his own half and fired a shot on goal toward Orlando City goalkeeper Brian Rowe - who was off his line. His strike proved to be the match winner as DC United won the game 1-0 on the night. Rooney who joined Major League Soccer (MLS) in 2018 has scored 9 goals coupled with 4 assists in 17 league appearances in the 2019/20 season.